hopobject.body: What do you do? best drugstore bb cream yahoo answers If you rewind and concentrate, there he is, gripping the shattered head of a bat and lurching, confused, toward Roger Clemens in the 2000 World Series. Or there you are, crying when he hit that home run against the Braves with the city still aching from 9/11, whether you cared about the Mets, Yankees or neither. These are lasting nights in the recent history of New York baseball.
